\n<Monster Maniac>There seem to be many types of monsters... but in reality,
there are only\C[24] two types\C[0]!!!

\n<Monster Maniac>In other words, it's either\C[24] Normal or something
else\C[0].

\n<Monster Maniac>Normal types are immune to special attacks, so even if you
use\C[24] Auto-attack, it will all be converted to normal
attacks\C[0]!

\n<Monster Maniac>Other types have weaknesses, so you can\C[24] hit them with
special attacks using Auto-attack\C[0]!

\n<Monster Maniac>Special attacks like anti-air missiles and torpedoes
can\C[24] deal massive damage but consume ammo\C[0]!

\n<Monster Maniac>If you run out of ammo, it'll just be a normal attack, so be
careful!
魔物の攻撃の種類

\n<Monster Maniac>There seem to be many types of monsters... but actually,
there are roughly\C[24] only two types\C[0]!!!
\n<Monster Maniac>That is to say, it's either\C[24] physical or magical\C[0].

\n<Monster Maniac>Physical attacks are subject to cut rates! When in\C[24]
Mode Aegis, damage is reduced\C[0]!

\n<Monster Maniac>Conversely, in Mode Ares, damage increases! Be careful not
to overdo it!

\n<Monster Maniac>On the other hand, magical attacks are not affected by\C[24]
cut rates\C[0]!

\n<Monster Maniac>Even if you're in Aegis mode, you can't reduce the damage!
In other words, there's no downside to being in Ares mode!
\n<Monster Maniac>Remember this!
魔物との戦い方

\n<Monster Maniac>After all, the basics are\C[24] analyzing the enemy\C[0]! If
you don't want to waste a turn, use an Analyzer!

\n<Monster Maniac>Against anything other than Normal types, you can deal big
damage with Auto-attack using ammo! If you're out of ammo,
run away!

\n<Monster Maniac>Also, if you absolutely want to conserve ammo, finishing
them off with a Power Knuckle is also an option!

\n<Monster Maniac>Against weaker enemies, go on the offensive with Ares mode!
When you need to heal, switch to Aegis mode and use Self
Repair!
